bug.short_desc: Submitting new bug against product with spaces in product name fails on bugzilla 4.2

long_desc.thetext:
What steps will reproduce the problem? 1. Create product in bugzilla with spaces in name, like my "Eulumdat Tools" 2. Create new bug against this product using Mylyn 3. Fail with below exception.
This is a regression as it did not occur when using Mylyn 3.6 or earlier.
-- Error Details -- Date: Sun Jun 10 22:09:08 CEST 2012 Message: Unexpected error during task submission Severity: Error Product: Eclipse 1.4.2.20120131-1457 (org.eclipse.epp.package.rcp.product) Plugin: org.eclipse.mylyn.tasks.core Session Data: eclipse.buildId=M20120208-0800 java.version=1.6.0_31 java.vendor=Apple Inc. BootLoader constants: OS=macosx, ARCH=x86_64, WS=cocoa, NL=en_US Framework arguments: -product org.eclipse.epp.package.rcp.product -keyring /Users/maarten/.eclipse_keyring -showlocation Command-line arguments: -os macosx -ws cocoa -arch x86_64 -product org.eclipse.epp.package.rcp.product -keyring /Users/maarten/.eclipse_keyring -showlocation
Exception Stack Trace: java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Invalid uri '/bugzilla/enter_bug.cgi?product=Eulumdat Tools': Invalid query at org.apache.commons.httpclient.HttpMethodBase.<init>(HttpMethodBase.java:222) at org.apache.commons.httpclient.methods.GetMethod.<init>(GetMethod.java:89) at org.eclipse.mylyn.internal.bugzilla.core.GzipGetMethod.<init>(GzipGetMethod.java:45) at org.eclipse.mylyn.internal.bugzilla.core.BugzillaClient.getTokenInternal(BugzillaClient.java:1246) at org.eclipse.mylyn.internal.bugzilla.core.BugzillaClient.postTaskDataInternal(BugzillaClient.java:1314) at org.eclipse.mylyn.internal.bugzilla.core.BugzillaClient.postTaskData(BugzillaClient.java:1205) at org.eclipse.mylyn.internal.bugzilla.core.BugzillaTaskDataHandler.postTaskData(BugzillaTaskDataHandler.java:415) at org.eclipse.mylyn.internal.tasks.core.sync.SubmitTaskJob.run(SubmitTaskJob.java:101) at org.eclipse.core.internal.jobs.Worker.run(Worker.java:54)

Created attachment 217422 Complaint about missing milestone when milestone is given
Must be because part of URL is lost because of not URLEncoded spaces

Thank you for changing back to normal (without comment) Steffen, but this failure to handle products with spaces (as allowed by bugzilla in the web interface) not only impacts the creation of new bugs, but also prevents a state change giving the error: Milestone required. you must select a target milestone for bug ... if you are going to accept it. Part of accepting a bug is giving an estimate of when it will be fixed.
Apparently the milestone part falls of the URL submitted because there is a space in it and the milestone check is done before the existing product check.
Suggest increasing to major again even when you are before 3.8 and Juno release...

I may be bitten by this one https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups#!topic/mozilla.support.bugzilla/Fltgd-aYmwk and this one https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=399078 so the seconed problem is caused by must have milestone on accept flag (In reply to comment #3) > Thank you for changing back to normal (without comment) Steffen, > but this failure to handle products with spaces (as allowed by bugzilla in the > web interface) not only impacts the creation of new bugs, but also prevents a > state change giving the error: > Milestone required. you must select a target milestone for bug ... if you are > going to accept it. Part of accepting a bug is giving an estimate of when it > will be fixed. > > Apparently the milestone part falls of the URL submitted because there is a > space in it and the milestone check is done before the existing product check. > > Suggest increasing to major again even when you are before 3.8 and Juno > release...
I may be bitten by this one https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=399078 described also here: https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups#!topic/mozilla.support.bugzilla/Fltgd-aYmwk so the second problem is caused by must have milestone on accept flag set to true and keeping default milestone. I fixed this in my setup and changed heading again
